A vintage-style illustration of an old-fashioned mustachioed craftsman at a wooden workbench, carefully assembling intricate brass gears and clockwork mechanisms into an ornate Victorian typing machine. The workshop is filled with warm amber lamplight, scattered blueprints showing form layouts and field diagrams, wooden drawers with small labeled compartments, and delicate tools hanging on pegboards. The craftsman wears a leather apron and magnifying spectacles, meticulously fitting tiny mechanical pieces together. Sepia and warm brown tones dominate, with touches of copper and gold metallics. Dust motes float in shafts of light from a frosted window. The scene evokes precision engineering, customization, and the art of building flexible, modular systems by hand.
